  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Full 13-factor assessment is reported; seven factors are assessed and six are flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite multiple factors with achieved levels below required levels, the assessment declares Medium assurance and an Accepted decision — an overstatement inconsistent with the structural evidence (COMPOUND-03 trigger).",
